originalText.text:
Be cautious when considering this parking garage. I called well in advance to inquire about the pricing, and they provided a certain rate over the phone. However, upon my arrival, the attendant unexpectedly doubled the fee and added an additional charge for a large car. The attendant's attitude was also quite rude and unpleasant.

To make matters worse, shortly after parking, my mother-in-law felt unwell and needed to return to the car just four minutes after I left it there. When I requested the car back, the attendant initially responded with impatience, saying he was busy (even though I told him about the medical problem of my mother-in-law) Eventually, he agreed to retrieve the car but I had to pay $50 (for 5 minutes of parking). When I asked for an explanation, he claimed it was because the machine recorded 6 minutes already, conveniently right after he told me to wait.

These individuals are scammers. I'll file a complaint with the DCWP.

originalText.text: Dec 7 2023 around 6 pm I went to pick up my car because I have a meeting in Manhattan for 2 days, so I reserved for two days. The first day I went to pick up my vehicle on the date and time listed above, the garage attendant there had a nasty attitude. I told him it wasn’t nice how he was acting. He responded by cancelling my second day reservation and told me “good luck finding parking tomorrow”. He then said there was nothing I can do about it. And he’s right, so far I haven’t found a contact number for the garage. They need better workers there.

originalText.text: Terrible service. Save yourself the headache and park elsewhere! We parked here on a Friday night, and there was only one worker. Took a long time to get your car back. When we returned, my car was parked up on a curb, 1" from a wall, and I was simply given the keys (had to climb in the passenger door). I found a line of deep scratches that the employee denied happened there. He said he couldn't do anything and we should call the next day. Conveniently, there's no website or phone listed on Google.

originalText.text: Worst garage in the city (and that's a strong statement). I previously lived in the building upstairs so I had a monthly spot in their lot. I ended up with at least 20 dents and scratches on my car from them backing it into the wall. The main attendant was incredibly rude and obnoxious and would complain about something every time I went to pick up my car. He also would tell me I needed to call 3 hours ahead if I wanted my car, even if the lot was half-empty. To make it worse, they didn't have an electronic system to request your car so you'd often have to call half a dozen times to just get them to pick up the phone to request it. I eventually wrote an email to complain to the manager (since he was never on-site). I never got a response but the next month they raised the price for my spot by $75 a month. Fortunately, I was moving out at that point anyway. I'd give it zero stars if I could.

originalText.text: This place was fine, don't be scared by the reviews. Yes oversize and tesla pay more but it's pretty clear when I booked on Spot Hero. Location is easy, they were quick on both drop off and pick up. No reason not to choose this place to park.
